> I always thought rngd's job was to read from a hardware random device (like /dev/hwrng) and feed /dev/random. Perhaps not?

No. Kernel doesn't have such a data tx channel between `/dev/hwrng` and `/dev/random`, so we need a service like `rngd` to read entropy from `/dev/hwrng` and feed it into the entropy pool of `/dev/random`, the latter will be used by security-sensitive applications.